      "message": "Done.\n\nGenerally I think Make targets are a good idea for tasks that require multiple Bazel commands, or Bazel commands with command-line flags (e.g. `make gazelle` from the repo root). I only envision //golden/Makefile going away if we don\u0027t have any such use cases under //golden after we\u0027re fully migrated to Bazel.\n\nThat said, I\u0027m completely open to having Make targets as aliases for simple Bazel commands if you think it\u0027ll make things easier.",
